, "nodes": [{"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "fnws91614", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "Customers occasionally order something that has already sold out elsewhere.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}]}, {"type": "LIST_ITEM", "id": "zq9fp1616", "nodes": [{"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "s7mf21617", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "Nobody can tell you, in real time, exactly how much of a given SKU you have across all channels combined.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}]}], "bulletedListData": {"indentation": 0}}, {"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "vecrl1619", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "These are not edge cases. They are indicators that your inventory system is reactive rather than real-time.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}, {"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "s4bu91621", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "And that gap is where revenue leaks.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}, {"type": "HEADING", "id": "why-fixing-it-drives-conversion", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "Why fixing it drives conversion", "decorations": []}}], "headingData": {"level": 2, "textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}, {"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "o2t0n1624", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "Accurate inventory does more than prevent errors. It actively improves performance:", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}, {"type": "BULLETED_LIST", "id": "frr4i1626", "nodes": [{"type": "LIST_ITEM", "id": "ki55h1627", "nodes": [{"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "owb3o1628", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "Customers are more likely to complete a purchase when availability is reliable.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}]}, {"type": "LIST_ITEM", "id": "s7ecr1630", "nodes": [{"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "z3vbm1631", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "Fewer cancellations mean fewer refunds and less friction.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}]}, {"type": "LIST_ITEM", "id": "fzfgj1633", "nodes": [{"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "im6qu1634", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "Marketing spend becomes more efficient because traffic is not wasted on unavailable products.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}]}, {"type": "LIST_ITEM", "id": "iwobf1636", "nodes": [{"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "snr7p1637", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "Teams spend less time fixing problems and more time scaling operations.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}]}], "bulletedListData": {"indentation": 0}}, {"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "ss4ce1639", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "Shopify\u2019s guide to omnichannel retail", "decorations": [{"type": "LINK", "linkData": {"link": {"url": "https://www.shopify.com/enterprise/omnichannel-retail", "target": "BLANK", "rel": {"nofollow": true}}}}, {"type": "UNDERLINE"}]}}, {"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": " highlights real-time inventory visibility as a key driver of conversion and customer satisfaction.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}, {"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "ndssr1642", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "In other words, inventory accuracy is not just an operations metric. It is a growth lever.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}, {"type": "HEADING", "id": "what-changed-in-our-case", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "What changed in our case", "decorations": []}}], "headingData": {"level": 2, "textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}, {"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "t87o51645", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "In the case of the retailer we worked with, the transformation came from unifying inventory into a single, real-time system across all channels.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}, {"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "0apvl1647", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "That meant:", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}, {"type": "BULLETED_LIST", "id": "x3zdy1649", "nodes": [{"type": "LIST_ITEM", "id": "03z8s1650", "nodes": [{"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "5sfto1651", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "One source of truth for stock levels.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}]}, {"type": "LIST_ITEM", "id": "vlukk1653", "nodes": [{"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "w84w91654", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "Instant updates across in-store, online, and marketplaces.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}]}, {"type": "LIST_ITEM", "id": "eoyc81656", "nodes": [{"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "3rct01657", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "Removal of manual reconciliation processes.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}]}, {"type": "LIST_ITEM", "id": "ywvc01659", "nodes": [{"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "ntv8o1660", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "Clear visibility for both operations and commercial teams.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}]}], "bulletedListData": {"indentation": 0}}, {"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "k4isd1662", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "The 42% uplift in conversion was not the result of better marketing. It was the removal of friction that should never have been there.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}, {"type": "HEADING", "id": "the-takeaway", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "The takeaway", "decorations": []}}], "headingData": {"level": 2, "textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}, {"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "3jlrl1665", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "If inventory accuracy is not something you can measure in real time, it is already costing you.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}, {"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "yfaku1667", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "The impact will not show up neatly in a report. It will show up in missed revenue, wasted ad spend, and frustrated customers.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}, {"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "i9pu61669", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "And the longer it goes unaddressed, the more it compounds.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}, {"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "fit5k1671", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "If you want, I can also make this more ", "decorations": []}}, {"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "Wix-friendly", "decorations": [{"type": "BOLD", "fontWeightValue": 700}]}}, {"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": " by formatting it with shorter paragraphs and cleaner heading structure for easier pasting.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}], "documentStyle": {}}'::jsonb, 3, false, false, '2026-07-11T08:05:18Z');
insert into blog_posts (title, slug, excerpt, content_text, rich_content, minutes_to_read, featured, pinned, first_published_at) values ('Fractional Leadership: When It Beats a Full-Time Hire', 'fractional-leadership-when-it-beats-a-full-time-hire', 'Not every business that needs senior digital leadership can justify — or afford — a full-time executive hire. That’s the gap fractional leadership is built for, and it is a better fit than most businesses expect. A full-time senior hire is a year-long commitment before you know if the fit is right, at a fully loaded cost that often exceeds what the role’s actual workload justifies in year one. Fractional leadership gives you the same calibre of decision-making, embedded in your team, scoped...', 'Not every business that needs senior digital leadership can justify — or afford — a full-time executive hire. That’s the gap fractional leadership is built for, and it is a better fit than most businesses expect. A full-time senior hire is a year-long commitment before you know if the fit is right, at a fully loaded cost that often exceeds what the role’s actual workload justifies in year one. Fractional leadership gives you the same calibre of decision-making, embedded in your team, scoped to the work that is actually there. According to Harvard Business Review, fractional leadership can be a practical way for growing organisations to access executive expertise without the cost of a full-time hire. Industry commentary also shows that fractional C-level leaders are being used to provide strategy, team leadership, and board-level decision-making without forcing businesses into permanent overhead too early Forbes. Why fractional leadership works Fractional leadership is not a diluted version of an executive hire. It is a deliberate operating model that gives businesses access to senior-level thinking without forcing them into a full-time structure too early. That matters because most growing companies do not need a permanent executive on day one. They need direction, structure, and momentum. They need someone who can clarify priorities, build the right systems, and make decisions that move the business forward without adding unnecessary cost or complexity. Exec Capital notes that fractional CTOs, CFOs, and CMOs are typically brought in to deliver high-level expertise, strategic clarity, and hands-on leadership where businesses need it most Exec Capital. A practical guide from VCMO also describes fractional leaders as executive-level decision-makers who influence strategy and lead teams, rather than acting as task-based support VCMO. The value is not just financial. Fractional leadership reduces hiring risk, shortens the time to impact, and gives businesses room to scale the function properly before making a permanent commitment. Where it fits best Fractional leadership tends to work best when a business is at an inflection point. That might be when: The marketing function is underperforming but not yet large enough to justify a full-time director. The business needs strategic leadership to align teams, but the day-to-day workload is still relatively light. A founder is carrying too much of the digital decision-making and needs senior support without a permanent hire. The company is entering a growth phase and wants to build the function properly before recruiting at full time. In these situations, fractional leadership acts as a bridge between where the business is now and where it needs to go next. The cost of hiring too early Hiring full time too early often creates more pressure than progress. A senior hire may be expensive, but the real cost is in misalignment: the role is too broad, the workload is too light, or the business is not yet ready to support the level of leadership it has hired. That can lead to frustration on both sides. The business expects transformation. The hire expects scope, autonomy, and scale. If neither is fully in place, the relationship can stall before it gets going. Fractional leadership avoids that trap by matching leadership capacity to actual demand. Instead of trying to force a full-time structure into an early-stage need, it lets the business build in the right order. When to make the switch Fractional leadership should usually be treated as a bridge, not a permanent state. It is the right model while the function is being built out, while priorities are still changing, and while the team is still defining what “good” looks like. The signal to switch to full time is usually workload. If the role is consistently more than a few days a week, and the business has enough clarity to define a full-time remit properly, that is the point where a permanent hire starts to make sense. By that stage, fractional leadership has already done part of the job. It has shaped the role, clarified the priorities, and created the conditions for a stronger full-time appointment. Why it is often the smarter choice The biggest advantage of fractional leadership is flexibility with seniority. You get experienced decision-making without taking on a full-time overhead before the business is ready for it. That makes it especially useful for companies that need to move quickly, stay lean, or avoid making a high-stakes hire too early. It is not a compromise. In many cases, it is the most commercially sensible way to access senior digital leadership. When used well, fractional leadership helps businesses make better decisions now and better hiring decisions later. Closing thought Not every business needs a full-time senior hire immediately. But many do need senior thinking, structure, and accountability before they are ready to commit to one. That is where fractional leadership earns its place: it gives the business exactly what it needs, when it needs it, and only at the level it can actually use.', '{"nodes": [{"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "9vtzk1085", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "Not every business that needs senior digital leadership can justify \u2014 or afford \u2014 a full-time executive hire. That\u2019s the gap fractional leadership is built for, and it is a better fit than most businesses expect.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}, {"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "d4q5x1087", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "A full-time senior hire is a year-long commitment before you know if the fit is right, at a fully loaded cost that often exceeds what the role\u2019s actual workload justifies in year one. Fractional leadership gives you the same calibre of decision-making, embedded in your team, scoped to the work that is actually there.", "decorations": []}}], "paragraphData": {"textStyle": {"textAlignment": "AUTO"}}}, {"type": "PARAGRAPH", "id": "zcddt1089", "nodes": [{"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "According to ", "decorations": []}}, {"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "Harvard Business Review", "decorations": [{"type": "LINK", "linkData": {"link": {"url": "https://hbr.org/podcast/2025/08/how-to-make-fractional-leadership-work", "target": "BLANK", "rel": {"nofollow": true}}}}, {"type": "UNDERLINE"}]}}, {"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": ", fractional leadership can be a practical way for growing organisations to access executive expertise without the cost of a full-time hire. Industry commentary also shows that fractional C-level leaders are being used to provide strategy, team leadership, and board-level decision-making without forcing businesses into permanent overhead too early ", "decorations": []}}, {"type": "TEXT", "id": "", "nodes": [], "textData": {"text": "Forbes", "decorations": [{"type": "LINK", "linkData": {"link": {"url": "https://www.forbes.com/councils/forbescoachescouncil/2025/08/25/how-to-make-the-most-of-fractional-leadership-20-tips-for-startu", "target": "BLANK", "rel": {"nofollow": tru